The Delta State Police Command said it had arrested a suspected kidnapper, one Onwuka Kelly, aged 23, in the Ughelli South Local Government Area of the state. It also said his victim, 37-year-old from Egbo-Urhie Community, was rescued unhurt. The police said exhibits recovered from the suspect, who is a member of a criminal gang, included one cut-to-size double barrel gun, one cut-to-size single barrel gun, and one live cartridge. City Round gathered that the arrest followed a distress call on the night of February 21, 2022, from an unidentified person from the Otu-Jeremi community in the area that some hoodlums stormed the community and kidnapped a young man in his Toyota Corolla car. Consequently, the Divisional Police Officer, Otu-Jeremi Division, was said to have deployed patrol teams in search of the hoodlums. It was, however, learnt that some policemen attached to the Counter-Terrorism Unit, Base 5, Warri, who were escorting their principal ran into the criminals and trailed them to Ekrokpe community. The hoodlums, upon sighting the police, opened fire, leading to a gun battle. The vehicle of the suspected kidnappers was said to have been demobilised by the team of policemen. The Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe, while confirming the incident, said an investigation was ongoing in the matter.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com